<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="553" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1593,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1593,1619]" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The only species of the 
<emphasis box="[555,633,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">tibialis</emphasis>
group with the following combination of characters: thorax, including legs dark brown, fore femur and distal ½ of fore tibia slightly paler, legs without femoral spines. Male unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="553" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1593,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1665,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was only known from the Nearctic region in 
<collectingCountry box="[974,1028,1665,1691]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1044,1115,1665,1691]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">Texas</collectingRegion>
). We provide the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[194,280,1701,1727]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[341,465,1701,1727]" name="Guatemala" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, and the Neotropical region. William L. Grogan (personal communication) recently informed us that he slides mounted 2 large (WL 
<quantity box="[692,793,1737,1763]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.84" pageId="3" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="2.84">2.84 mm</quantity>
) females from 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1084,1737,1763]" name="Guatemala" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
collected during 2012 with CR 0.93−0.94, which is slightly smaller than the 
<typeStatus box="[657,755,1773,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="553">holotype</typeStatus>
(CR 0.96).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
